snippet: West Register Street by the narrow alley running now between the New Register House and the new Cafe Royal. This little paved foot-path was, in the time of Ambrose's, a green lane called Gabriel's Road, leading diagonally across the New Town to Silvermills, and it is said still to claim its ancient privilege of a right of way.

snippet: I pricked up my small ears at once, and with a quick look ofintelligence, followed her out of the shop. We got as far as West Register Street, and then she suddenlypulled up. " Ah ! he's forgotten to put in the worsted jackets."
